in a marine insurance policy...

1757
01:51:39,200 --> 01:51:42,180
is anything that you can't avoid.

1758
01:51:42,280 --> 01:51:43,620
Eggs break...

1759
01:51:43,720 --> 01:51:45,180
chocolate melts...

1760
01:51:45,280 --> 01:51:47,500
glass shatters...

1761
01:51:47,600 --> 01:51:52,342
and Doc wondered what that meant
when it applied to ex-old ladies.

1762
01:52:03,480 --> 01:52:05,309
SORTILÈGE: What's on your mind, Doc?

1763
01:52:06,320 --> 01:52:08,263
Besides the usual?

1764
01:52:11,560 --> 01:52:13,150
I don't know.

1765
01:52:14,720 --> 01:52:17,300
I'm like, you know...

1766
01:52:18,720 --> 01:52:22,541
working myself
into a brain freeze here, Lège.

1767
01:52:25,320 --> 01:52:27,540
Well, put it another way:

1768
01:52:27,640 --> 01:52:30,391
What's gonna nag at you
in the middle of the night?

1769
01:52:30,880 --> 01:52:34,268
What's gonna nag at me
in the middle of the night?

1770
01:52:36,760 --> 01:52:38,703
Little kid blues?

1771
01:52:40,520 --> 01:52:42,668
Saxophone players?

1772
01:52:47,720 --> 01:52:49,629
You know, whatever...

1773
01:52:50,840 --> 01:52:55,104
he meant to do...
Coy, you know, mistakes aside, and...

1774
01:52:58,040 --> 01:53:01,667
Nobody deserves to go through life
without seeing their daughter.

1775
01:53:02,360 --> 01:53:04,303
That don't sit well with me.

1776
01:53:09,400 --> 01:53:11,184
Then go get them.

1777
01:53:13,480 --> 01:53:15,020
- MAN: Put it on your desk.
- PENNY: Thank you.

1778
01:53:15,120 --> 01:53:17,860
- Whoa. What are you doing here? Yeah.
- "Whoa"?

1779
01:53:17,960 --> 01:53:21,460
Wanted to see if you were free for dinner.
I didn't mean to freak you out.

1780
01:53:21,560 --> 01:53:23,100
Are you all right?

1781
01:53:23,200 --> 01:53:25,382
- Am I?
- Are you?

1782
01:53:26,200 --> 01:53:28,420
Should I call security?

1783
01:53:28,520 --> 01:53:30,820
- PENNY: No, Rhus.
- I don't think we need...

1784
01:53:30,920 --> 01:53:33,148
This is the one I was telling you about.

1785
01:53:44,360 --> 01:53:45,460
Yeah?

1786
01:53:45,560 --> 01:53:47,460
You know your pals
have Mickey Wolfmann?

1787
01:53:47,560 --> 01:53:51,140
What? The FBI? I mean, we suspected,
but we couldn't prove it.

1788
01:53:51,240 --> 01:53:52,860
Well, I saw him in their custody.

1789
01:53:52,960 --> 01:53:54,949
- You saw him?
- Yeah.

1790
01:53:57,080 --> 01:53:59,100
Would you be willing
to let me depone you?

1791
01:53:59,200 --> 01:54:00,580
- Sure would.
- You would?

1792
01:54:00,680 --> 01:54:01,860
What is it?

1793
01:54:01,960 --> 01:54:04,940
You, me, a tape machine,
maybe another DDA to witness it.

1794
01:54:05,040 --> 01:54:07,820
- All right, I need something from you though.
- What?

1795
01:54:07,920 --> 01:54:10,022
I need to look up somebody's jacket.

1796
01:54:10,640 --> 01:54:13,580
That's it? That's no big deal.
We do that all the time.

1797
01:54:13,680 --> 01:54:16,670
What, you break into officially
sealed records all the time?

1798
01:54:17,160 --> 01:54:19,228
Grow up. What's the name on the file?

1799
01:54:20,720 --> 01:54:22,788
Adrian Prussia.

1800
01:54:34,400 --> 01:54:37,700
SORTILÈGE: As if looking for something
he didn't want to find...

1801
01:54:37,800 --> 01:54:41,340
it became clear as vodka
you keep in the icebox...

1802
01:54:41,440 --> 01:54:46,220
that, whatever the connection between
the L.A.P.D. and Adrian Prussia...

1803
01:54:46,320 --> 01:54:49,700
he might as well have been working
for them as a contract killer...

1804
01:54:49,800 --> 01:54:52,551
doing deeds for them
they couldn't do for themselves.

1805
01:54:53,200 --> 01:54:58,700
Time after time, he was pulled in,
questioned, arraigned, indicted, no matter.

1806
01:54:58,800 --> 01:55:01,220
Somehow the cases
never quite got to trial...

1807
01:55:01,320 --> 01:55:04,902
each being bargained down
in the interest of justice...

1808
01:55:05,040 --> 01:55:08,180
not to mention Adrian,
who invariably walked.

1809
01:55:08,280 --> 01:55:11,100
And one of those deeds
appeared to be labeled...

1810
01:55:11,200 --> 01:55:15,820
"the justifiable homicide"
of one of the L.A.P.D.'s very own:

1811
01:55:15,920 --> 01:55:18,660
Vincent Indelicato.

1812
01:55:18,760 --> 01:55:20,340
Otherwise known as...

1813
01:55:20,440 --> 01:55:21,940
Bigfoot's partner.

1814
01:55:22,040 --> 01:55:23,426
DOC: Bigfoot.

1815
01:55:24,520 --> 01:55:26,100
SORTILÈGE: Bigfoot's partner?

1816
01:55:26,200 --> 01:55:28,500
Fucking Bigfoot's partner?

1817
01:55:28,600 --> 01:55:31,300
Oh, fuck.

1818
01:55:31,400 --> 01:55:36,500
SORTILÈGE: Bigfoot's air of possessed
melancholy now began to make sense.

1819
01:55:36,600 --> 01:55:38,623
This was mourning, all right.

1820
01:55:39,160 --> 01:55:40,260
And it was deep.

1821
01:55:40,360 --> 01:55:41,980
MAN: This your new partner, Bigfoot?

1822
01:55:42,080 --> 01:55:45,340
Want a banana, Adrian?
Bend over and I'll stick it in for you.

1823
01:55:45,440 --> 01:55:47,300
ADRIAN: Fuck you and fuck your banana.

1824
01:55:47,400 --> 01:55:49,500
SORTILÈGE: Oh, man, oh, man.

1825
01:55:49,600 --> 01:55:54,260
Never be surprised at the levels
of disrespect within the L.A.P.D.

1826
01:55:54,360 --> 01:55:58,660
But this was downright nasty,
not to mention unprofessional.

1827
01:55:58,760 --> 01:56:02,820
This bond between partners was nearly
the only thing Doc had ever found...

1828
01:56:02,920 --> 01:56:05,466
to admire about the L.A.P.D.

1829
01:56:06,200 --> 01:56:09,224
BIGFOOT: You know, there's places
you don't wanna go, Doc.

1830
01:56:10,280 --> 01:56:12,144
Go back to the beach.

1831
01:56:12,640 --> 01:56:15,107
You smell like a patchouli fart.

1832
01:56:16,880 --> 01:56:18,903
SORTILÈGE: So here's Doc.

1833
01:56:20,440 --> 01:56:22,820
Midnight, pitch-dark...

1834
01:56:22,920 --> 01:56:25,700
can't remember whether
they drained the pool or not...

1835
01:56:25,800 --> 01:56:28,346
but, hey, what the fuck's it matter?

1836
01:56:28,760 --> 01:56:31,540
He bounced once, twice...

1837
01:56:31,640 --> 01:56:34,940
and then off the end of the board
in a blind cannonball...

1838
01:56:35,040 --> 01:56:38,700
down into old karma
with Adrian Prussia...

1839
01:56:38,800 --> 01:56:40,700
who had not only shot at him once...

1840
01:56:40,800 --> 01:56:44,740
but threatened him with a Carl
Yastrzemski Special baseball bat.

1841
01:56:44,840 --> 01:56:47,980
All this leaving Doc to wonder:

1842
01:56:48,080 --> 01:56:50,626
"Where's the partner to watch my back?"

1843
01:56:52,840 --> 01:56:54,624
ADRIAN: Far out, man.

1844
01:56:55,280 --> 01:56:56,711
Right.

1845
01:56:57,280 --> 01:56:59,382
Psychedelic.

1846
01:57:00,160 --> 01:57:01,500
Done.

1847
01:57:07,280 --> 01:57:09,860
So you're here about...?

1848
01:57:10,440 --> 01:57:12,304
Good question.

1849
01:57:12,440 --> 01:57:14,190
Uh...

1850
01:57:16,720 --> 01:57:20,267
Wait a minute. This is bullshit.

1851
01:57:20,920 --> 01:57:22,226
I remember you.

1852
01:57:23,120 --> 01:57:26,300
You're that kid from Fritz's shop
out in Santa Monica, right?

1853
01:57:26,400 --> 01:57:27,547
Yeah.

1854
01:57:27,680 --> 01:57:30,820
So, what you up to these days?
Skip tracing?

1855
01:57:30,920 --> 01:57:33,182
Or did you go into the priesthood?

1856
01:57:34,000 --> 01:57:35,431
PI.

1857
01:57:36,040 --> 01:57:39,587
Heh. They gave you a license?

1858
01:57:40,640 --> 01:57:42,504
So who sent you here?

1859
01:57:42,720 --> 01:57:44,620
- Mm. Uh...
- Who are you working for today?

1860
01:57:44,720 --> 01:57:47,505
All on spec. All on my own time.

1861
01:57:49,720 --> 01:57:51,549
Wrong answer.

1862
01:57:52,640 --> 01:57:56,825
How much of your own time
do you think you got left, kid?

1863
01:57:57,840 --> 01:58:00,625
I was just about to ask.

1864
01:58:02,360 --> 01:58:04,660
Howdy, Puck.

1865
01:58:04,760 --> 01:58:06,380
Do I know you?

1866
01:58:06,480 --> 01:58:08,700
I don't think I do.

1867
01:58:08,800 --> 01:58:12,460
I don't know, you must remind me
of someone I ran into someplace.

1868
01:58:12,560 --> 01:58:13,820
My mistake.

1869
01:58:13,920 --> 01:58:17,263
I have a busy day ahead...

1870
01:58:18,400 --> 01:58:20,821
and I know nothing...

1871
01:58:21,920 --> 01:58:23,863
of any of this.

1872
01:58:31,120 --> 01:58:32,745
What are you doing here?

1873
01:58:34,800 --> 01:58:38,302
I was just, uh... talking to Adrian.

1874
01:58:40,680 --> 01:58:42,270
Mm.

1875
01:58:42,680 --> 01:58:44,305
It's these, uh...

1876
01:58:45,520 --> 01:58:47,900
various cases I'm working on.

1877
01:58:48,000 --> 01:58:49,590
And, uh...

1878
01:58:51,800 --> 01:58:54,983
mm, Glen Charlock...

1879
01:58:55,840 --> 01:58:59,626
and, uh... Vincent Indelicato...

1880
01:59:07,040 --> 01:59:08,141
[LAUGHING]

1881
01:59:13,160 --> 01:59:14,780
and, uh...

1882
01:59:14,880 --> 01:59:16,823
where'd...

1883
01:59:18,720 --> 01:59:20,185
you...

1884
01:59:20,680 --> 01:59:22,191
get that...?

1885
01:59:24,520 --> 01:59:26,620
That necklace...

1886
01:59:26,720 --> 01:59:28,740
it looks funny on you.

1887
01:59:28,840 --> 01:59:31,386
Big man, small necklace.

1888
01:59:33,120 --> 01:59:36,190
Acid invites you through a door.

1889
01:59:36,800 --> 01:59:39,700
PCP opens that door...

1890
01:59:39,800 --> 01:59:41,300
shoves you through it...

1891
01:59:41,400 --> 01:59:43,946
slams the door behind you...

1892
01:59:44,840 --> 01:59:45,987
and locks it.

1893
01:59:49,760 --> 01:59:51,385
[DOC GRUNTS]

1894
01:59:54,320 --> 01:59:56,787
Special treat for you today, doper.

1895
01:59:57,360 --> 01:59:59,340
Just got it in a shipment...

1896
01:59:59,440 --> 02:00:01,542
of pure Number 4.

1897
02:00:02,720 --> 02:00:05,460
Ain't a white guy's finger laid on it...

1898
02:00:05,560 --> 02:00:07,981
between the Golden Triangle...

1899
02:00:09,800 --> 02:00:12,221
and your own throbbing vein.

1900
02:00:13,160 --> 02:00:15,581
Just let me step out here...

1901
02:00:16,160 --> 02:00:17,944
and I'll go get you some.

1902
02:00:20,120 --> 02:00:21,824
[GRUNTING]

1903
02:00:25,000 --> 02:00:26,864
Don't go away now.

1904
02:00:36,520 --> 02:00:39,271
[MUTTERING]

1905
02:00:57,080 --> 02:00:58,227
[GASPING]

1906
02:01:19,880 --> 02:01:21,061
[FOOTSTEPS]

1907
02:01:34,040 --> 02:01:37,100
[GRUNTING]

1908
02:01:37,200 --> 02:01:38,665
MAN: Puck!

1909
02:01:44,840 --> 02:01:46,385
Pucky!

1910
02:01:54,320 --> 02:01:56,991
[PANTING]

1911
02:02:04,920 --> 02:02:06,670
Did I hit you?

1912
02:02:34,760 --> 02:02:36,305
Bigfoot?

1913
02:02:36,760 --> 02:02:38,624
What the fuck?

1914
02:02:40,320 --> 02:02:42,700
BIGFOOT:
Did you take care of them okay, Doc?

1915
02:02:42,800 --> 02:02:47,220
You fucking lunatic! What is this?

1916
02:02:47,320 --> 02:02:49,980
I'm in enough shit personally
with the captain...

1917
02:02:50,080 --> 02:02:52,786
and I've seen you on the range.
Nice work.

1918
02:02:54,440 --> 02:02:55,826
What are you...?

1919
02:02:56,800 --> 02:03:00,220
And that there,
is that what I think it is? Huh?

1920
02:03:00,320 --> 02:03:04,140
There's one of or two of them.
There's more. Enough left for evidence.

1921
02:03:04,240 --> 02:03:06,940
Man, Bigfoot, I saw the movie.

1922
02:03:07,040 --> 02:03:10,660
As I recall, that character
comes to a bad end.

1923
02:03:10,760 --> 02:03:12,260
Put the gun away, Doc.

1924
02:03:12,360 --> 02:03:13,940
- What?
- The gun. Put it away.

1925
02:03:14,040 --> 02:03:17,220
