02:05:43,400 --> 02:05:45,548
Japonica's dad?

1949
02:05:46,280 --> 02:05:48,060
Oh...

1950
02:05:48,160 --> 02:05:49,980
What happened this time?

1951
02:05:50,080 --> 02:05:54,742
FENWAY: You have something that belongs to
some people I represent, and they'd like it back.

1952
02:05:55,760 --> 02:05:59,500
Oh. So you're a principal in all this?

1953
02:05:59,600 --> 02:06:02,940
FENWAY: It's only because of me
and our small transaction over Japonica...

1954
02:06:03,040 --> 02:06:05,180
that you're still alive.

1955
02:06:05,280 --> 02:06:07,587
Ever so grateful, sir.

1956
02:06:09,520 --> 02:06:11,420
So, what do we do?

1957
02:06:11,520 --> 02:06:13,780
I suppose someone wants their, uh...

1958
02:06:13,880 --> 02:06:15,020
[MIMICS INHALING]

1959
02:06:15,120 --> 02:06:16,301
back?

1960
02:06:16,800 --> 02:06:22,031
FENWAY: Why don't we meet this evening at 6:00
at my club, The Portola, in Elysian Park.

1961
02:06:23,200 --> 02:06:25,860
Mm-hm. Is there a dress code?

1962
02:06:25,960 --> 02:06:28,381
FENWAY: A jacket and tie, if possible.

1963
02:06:30,000 --> 02:06:31,829
I'll see you then.

1964
02:06:43,760 --> 02:06:45,783
FENWAY: Mr. Sportello.

1965
02:06:46,480 --> 02:06:48,309
DOC: Mr. Fenway.

1966
02:06:53,600 --> 02:06:55,304
[CLEARS THROAT]

1967
02:07:03,400 --> 02:07:05,821
To a peaceful...

1968
02:07:06,760 --> 02:07:08,385
resolution.

1969
02:07:14,200 --> 02:07:16,985
How's the family?

1970
02:07:17,440 --> 02:07:19,144
Japonica's...

1971
02:07:19,800 --> 02:07:21,823
doing fine, if that's what you mean.

1972
02:07:23,760 --> 02:07:25,260
You know...

1973
02:07:25,360 --> 02:07:29,545
I think I saw old Japonica
the other day at my doctor's office.

1974
02:07:31,120 --> 02:07:34,660
You ever run across a dentist
named Rudy Blatnoyd?

1975
02:07:34,760 --> 02:07:38,900
The son of a bitch who until recently
was corrupting my daughter?

1976
02:07:39,000 --> 02:07:41,660
Yes, I do seem to recall the name.

1977
02:07:41,760 --> 02:07:45,460
He perished in a trampoline
accident, didn't he?

1978
02:07:45,560 --> 02:07:48,425
L.A.P.D. aren't so sure
it was an accident.

1979
02:07:49,080 --> 02:07:51,387
And you'd like to know if I did it?

1980
02:07:54,080 --> 02:07:56,228
What possible motive would I have?

1981
02:07:57,680 --> 02:08:00,140
Just because the man preyed on...

1982
02:08:00,240 --> 02:08:03,264
an emotionally vulnerable child?

1983
02:08:03,960 --> 02:08:06,140
Forced her to engage
in sexual practices...

1984
02:08:06,240 --> 02:08:09,700
that might appall
even a sophisticate like yourself?

1985
02:08:09,800 --> 02:08:12,540
Does that mean I'd have any reason
to see his miserable...

1986
02:08:12,640 --> 02:08:14,460
pedophile career come to an end?

1987
02:08:14,560 --> 02:08:18,745
What a vindictive person
you must imagine me.

1988
02:08:19,160 --> 02:08:20,860
Mm...

1989
02:08:20,960 --> 02:08:26,420
Mm, I did suspect he was fucking
his receptionist, but what dentist doesn't?

1990
02:08:26,520 --> 02:08:29,020
It's some oath they all take
in dentist school.

1991
02:08:29,120 --> 02:08:34,780
Anyhow, it's a long way
from strange and weird sex, isn't it?

1992
02:08:34,880 --> 02:08:37,100
What about when he forced
my girl to listen...

1993
02:08:37,200 --> 02:08:41,385
to original cast albums of Broadway
musicals while he had his way with her?

1994
02:08:44,840 --> 02:08:48,501
Or the tastelessness of the decor...

1995
02:08:49,880 --> 02:08:52,660
of resort hotel rooms he took her to...

1996
02:08:52,760 --> 02:08:56,100
during endodontist conventions.

1997
02:08:56,200 --> 02:08:57,745
The wallpaper.

1998
02:08:58,800 --> 02:09:00,868
The lamps.

1999
02:09:04,000 --> 02:09:06,910
Japonica's of legal age now, isn't she?

2000
02:09:07,360 --> 02:09:10,145
In a father's eye,
they're always too young.

2001
02:09:18,080 --> 02:09:19,740
To the matter at hand.

2002
02:09:19,840 --> 02:09:23,940
Those I represent are prepared to offer you
a generous compensation package...

2003
02:09:24,040 --> 02:09:26,871
for the safe return of their property.

2004
02:09:27,920 --> 02:09:30,626
Suppose it didn't have to be
in the form of money.

2005
02:09:31,760 --> 02:09:34,101
Well, money would be a lot easier.

2006
02:09:36,240 --> 02:09:39,460
There's a saxophone player
named Coy Harlingen.

2007
02:09:39,560 --> 02:09:43,980
He's been working undercover for different
anti-subversive outfits, including the L.A.P.D.

2008
02:09:44,080 --> 02:09:48,540
And he's come to feel lately
that he made the wrong career choice.

2009
02:09:48,640 --> 02:09:50,900
It lost him his family, his freedom.

2010
02:09:51,000 --> 02:09:53,307
And like you, he only has one daughter.

2011
02:09:53,920 --> 02:09:55,420
Please.

2012
02:09:55,520 --> 02:09:59,220
Okay. Well, he wants out.

2013
02:09:59,320 --> 02:10:01,820
And I think I can square it
with the heat.

2014
02:10:01,920 --> 02:10:05,660
But there's this other bunch,
Vigilant California.

2015
02:10:05,760 --> 02:10:08,101
And, well, whoever's running them,
of course...

2016
02:10:12,800 --> 02:10:16,900
My guess is they'd prefer he not disclose
any confidential information.

2017
02:10:17,000 --> 02:10:18,943
Last thing he'd ever do.

2018
02:10:19,400 --> 02:10:20,990
Your personal guarantee?

2019
02:10:21,120 --> 02:10:23,507
I'll go after him myself
if he tries anything.

2020
02:10:24,720 --> 02:10:26,549
Then we have a deal.

2021
02:10:28,200 --> 02:10:29,940
That's all you wanted?

2022
02:10:30,040 --> 02:10:32,302
No money now? Are you sure?

2023
02:10:35,240 --> 02:10:39,425
Well, now, how much money would I have to
take from you so I wouldn't lose your respect?

2024
02:10:41,120 --> 02:10:44,180
It's a bit late for that, Mr. Sportello.

2025
02:10:44,280 --> 02:10:48,704
People like you lose all claim to respect
the first time they pay anybody rent.

2026
02:10:53,080 --> 02:10:55,860
Well, I may not be as well-connected...

2027
02:10:55,960 --> 02:10:59,826
and for sure, not as much
into revenge as you folks are...

2028
02:11:01,320 --> 02:11:04,020
but if you're jiving with me, my man...

2029
02:11:04,120 --> 02:11:05,220
I say to you:

2030
02:11:05,320 --> 02:11:07,024
[CLICKS TONGUE]

2031
02:11:08,200 --> 02:11:09,711
Hmm?

2032
02:11:13,680 --> 02:11:16,545
So where we gonna do this handoff?

2033
02:11:17,680 --> 02:11:18,740
[SAM COOKE'S "(WHAT A) WONDERFUL
WORLD" PLAYING ON RADIO]

2034
02:11:18,840 --> 02:11:20,624
Don't know much about history

2035
02:11:21,480 --> 02:11:24,345
Don't know much biology

2036
02:11:25,320 --> 02:11:28,220
Don't know much about science books

2037
02:11:28,320 --> 02:11:31,740
Golden Fang operatives, 12 o'clock.
Fast approaching.

2038
02:11:31,840 --> 02:11:33,271
Look sharp.

2039
02:11:36,600 --> 02:11:39,260
And I know that if you love me too

2040
02:11:39,360 --> 02:11:42,350
What a wonderful world it would be

2041
02:11:44,080 --> 02:11:46,945
Don't know much about geography

2042
02:11:47,680 --> 02:11:50,704
Don't know much trigonometry

2043
02:11:51,400 --> 02:11:54,265
DOC:
All right, you got the keys in here?

2044
02:11:55,280 --> 02:11:57,542
Don't know what a slide rule is for

2045
02:11:58,920 --> 02:12:01,751
But I do know, one and one is two

2046
02:12:02,280 --> 02:12:05,420
And if this world could be with you

2047
02:12:05,520 --> 02:12:08,624
What a wonderful world this would be

2048
02:12:10,800 --> 02:12:12,709
Now, what's all this?

2049
02:12:13,320 --> 02:12:16,420
It's a credit card.
Don't hippies have them?

2050
02:12:16,520 --> 02:12:20,100
Yeah, I must've meant that why is
your mother handing me this?

2051
02:12:20,200 --> 02:12:23,543
- It's not for you.
- Ah. Uh...

2052
02:12:24,480 --> 02:12:28,740
You're supposed to tell him: "Well done.
Welcome back to the main herd.

2053
02:12:28,840 --> 02:12:30,420
Safe journeys."

2054
02:12:30,520 --> 02:12:32,180
That's journeys, plural.

2055
02:12:32,280 --> 02:12:34,780
"Well done. Welcome back to the herd.
Safe journeys."

2056
02:12:34,880 --> 02:12:37,142
Okay, I guess I can remember that.

2057
02:12:47,360 --> 02:12:49,460
- GIRL: What are you looking at?
- Huh?

2058
02:12:49,560 --> 02:12:50,866
What?

2059
02:12:57,080 --> 02:13:01,151
So you guys been working
for the Golden Fang long?

2060
02:13:12,160 --> 02:13:13,466
Okay.

2061
02:13:23,280 --> 02:13:26,384
Sassy, little girl. Nasty. Mean.

2062
02:13:34,480 --> 02:13:37,026
There's nothing? All right.

2063
02:14:00,480 --> 02:14:01,700
Everything's cool.

2064
02:14:01,800 --> 02:14:05,220
I'm officially off everybody's payroll.
Burke Stodger just called me.

2065
02:14:05,320 --> 02:14:06,940
You're a dangerous hombre.

2066
02:14:07,040 --> 02:14:08,380
Drive.

2067
02:14:31,320 --> 02:14:32,751
You all right?

2068
02:14:34,600 --> 02:14:36,429
I'm nervous.

2069
02:14:37,080 --> 02:14:38,306
Yeah.

2070
02:14:41,120 --> 02:14:43,268
You know what the Indians say.

2071
02:14:44,120 --> 02:14:45,900
- You saved my life...
- Ugh...

2072
02:14:46,000 --> 02:14:47,940
now you're responsible for it.

2073
02:14:48,040 --> 02:14:50,791
No, man. No, that's not true.

2074
02:14:52,040 --> 02:14:54,302
Some hippie made that up, man.

2075
02:14:55,480 --> 02:14:58,345
You saved your own life, man.
Now you get to live it.

2076
02:15:48,160 --> 02:15:51,946
[HOPE LAUGHING]

2077
02:15:53,960 --> 02:15:55,550
HOPE: Baby!

2078
02:16:13,960 --> 02:16:17,540
SORTILÈGE:
Yet there is no avoiding time.

2079
02:16:17,640 --> 02:16:19,981
The sea of time.

2080
02:16:20,880 --> 02:16:24,500
The sea of memory and forgetfulness.

2081
02:16:24,600 --> 02:16:28,980
The years of promise gone
and unrecoverable.

2082
02:16:29,080 --> 02:16:33,100
Of the land almost allowed
to claim its better destiny...

2083
02:16:33,200 --> 02:16:37,940
only to have that claim jumped
by evildoers known all too well...

2084
02:16:38,040 --> 02:16:39,580
and taken instead...

2085
02:16:39,680 --> 02:16:44,660
and held hostage to the future
we must live in now, forever.

2086
02:16:44,760 --> 02:16:46,540
DOC: So who got her?

2087
02:16:46,640 --> 02:16:48,420
Department of Justice.

2088
02:16:48,520 --> 02:16:50,820
So, like, uh... justice was served?

2089
02:16:50,920 --> 02:16:54,620
That's exactly right, Doc.
That's exactly right.

2090
02:16:54,720 --> 02:17:00,065
SORTILÈGE: May we trust this blessed ship
is bound for some better shore.

2091
02:17:00,640 --> 02:17:02,981
Risen and redeemed.

2092
02:17:03,400 --> 02:17:08,904
Where the American fate
mercifully failed to transpire.

2093
02:17:11,520 --> 02:17:12,667
[COUGHING]

2094
02:17:17,040 --> 02:17:19,905
[GLASS BREAKING]

2095
02:17:22,560 --> 02:17:24,220
Don't get Up.

2096
02:17:24,320 --> 02:17:26,627
Bigfoot. Man...

2097
02:17:27,320 --> 02:17:29,582
You smashed down my door?

2098
02:17:30,120 --> 02:17:31,346
Come on.

2099
02:17:31,680 --> 02:17:35,546
After a long and busy day
of civil rights violations...

2100
02:17:36,200 --> 02:17:39,986
I found myself in the neighborhood
and compelled to drop in.

2101
02:17:40,400 --> 02:17:45,180
Just to check and see the current state
of affairs of my old stomping grounds.

2102
02:17:45,280 --> 02:17:49,060
Seeing as your effort to keep lines
of communication had been...

2103
02:17:49,160 --> 02:17:50,460
limited.

2104
02:17:50,560 --> 02:17:52,469
To say the least.

2105
02:17:53,360 --> 02:17:56,111
Well, I've been busy.

2106
02:17:56,760 --> 02:18:00,706
Trying to figure out which side
of the Zig-Zag paper's the sticky side?

2107
02:18:03,560 --> 02:18:05,344
Give it to me.

2108
02:18:33,520 --> 02:18:34,820
[IN UNISON] Listen.

2109
02:18:34,920 --> 02:18:36,940
- I'm sorry about last night.
- I'm sorry about last night

2110
02:18:37,040 --> 02:18:38,540
- You?
- You?

2111
02:18:38,640 --> 02:18:40,663
Why should you be sorry?

2112
02:18:42,360 --> 02:18:44,189
Weird.

2113
02:19:13,520 --> 02:19:15,622
Uh...

2114
02:19:17,560 --> 02:19:19,583
[TRAY CLANGING]

2115
02:19:19,720 --> 02:19:21,948
Are you okay, brother?

2116
02:19:26,320 --> 02:19:28,502
I'm not your brother.

2117
02:19:29,920 --> 02:19:32,671
No, but you could use a keeper.

2118
02:19:52,240 --> 02:19:54,060
SHASTA: Remember that day?

2119
02:19:54,160 --> 02:19:57,628
The Ouija board set us off
into that big storm?

2120
02:20:00,440 --> 02:20:03,020
This feels the same way tonight.

2121
02:20:06,040 --> 02:20:07,744
Just us.

2122
02:20:08,320 --> 02:20:09,865
Together.

2123
02:20:15,560 --> 02:20:18,391
Almost like being underwater.

2124
02:20:22,200 --> 02:20:24,109
The world...

2125
02:20:25,960 --> 02:20:27,789
everything...

2126
02:20:30,240 --> 02:20:32,661
gone someplace else.

2127
02:20:37,800 --> 02:20:40,870
Just figured it was
Sortilège setting us up.

2128
02:20:43,840 --> 02:20:45,180
No.

2129
02:20:45,280 --> 02:20:47,220
Her Ouija board and...

2130
02:20:47,320 --> 02:20:51,220
- She knows things, Doc.
- Mm.

2131
02:20:53,840 --> 02:20:56,591
Maybe about us that we don't know.

2132
02:21:12,200 --> 02:21:14,985
This don't mean we're back together.

2133
02:21:18,360 --> 02:21:19,825
[SHASTA CHUCKLES]

2134
02:21:22,560 --> 02:21:24,424
Of course not.

2135
02:28:39,160 --> 02:28:41,262
[ENGLISH - US - SDH]